+THUMBS UP IF I'M HELPFUL+ This was the first Tower Defense game I ever played on my phone. I participated in the BETA for the game in 2011. The game is perfect for what it is, it doesn't try to be anything else. One of the best parts of the game is that it doesn't beg for your money like BloonsTD does. Upgrades are purchased with the in game currency earned through playing. It is very easy to earn cash in the game. The way the game is played, is you create lanes by building towers. Your goal is to create a track out of Robo Towers that the enemy can't get through to the other side. To avoid confusion, tower variants are upgrades of the 3 base towers you start out with. That way you're not navigating, wondering what to pick next. It's very simple, and straight up Tower Defense. An amazing game that I personally have supported for a very long time.

The gameplay and tower types provided by Robo Defense are fairly vanilla, but the reward points system and the upgrades available give the game a lot of replayability.  Biggest complaint is probably the fact that the reward points system is poorly explained and there is no mechanism for rolling back your choices. When you choose one of the bigger upgrades, all other large upgrades go up in cost, by a large margin at the outset. Some of these upgrades are poorly explained or just plain bad, which can lead to a lot of buyer's remorse.  Mine "towers" are especially poorly explained and the mechanic they use is clunky. Perhaps an actual tower that lays down mines would work better, or a different option or mechanic entirely.  These complaints aside, it's still a game that will keep you busily racking up points for many hours. Well worth it.
